This paper discusses the security threat of DoS attacks in IoT systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the unique characteristics of IoT devices, such as their limited computing power and memory, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper presents a model that mimics the behavior of IoT devices, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses stochastic model checking to analyze the efficiency of different implementations of IoT systems, which suggests that it may fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or software engineering (cs.SE).
